    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect loop bounds in HARQ indication packing function\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_harq_indication_body_value` function in the nfapi library could potentially access memory beyond the allocated `harq_pdu_list` array if `number_of_harqs` exceeded `NFAPI_HARQ_IND_MAX_PDU`. This could lead to memory corruption or segmentation faults when processing HARQ indications with invalid counts.\n\nThis fix adds a bounds check assertion to prevent out-of-bounds array access.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Added assertion to validate `total_number_of_pdus` against `NFAPI_HARQ_IND_MAX_PDU` in `pack_harq_indication_body_value` function.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Create a HARQ indication with `number_of_harqs` set to a value larger than 100\n2. Process this indication through the packing function\n3. Observe potential segmentation fault or memory corruption when accessing `harq_pdu_list[i]` for indices beyond the allocated array bounds\n\nThe fix prevents this by asserting that `total_number_of_pdus` is within valid bounds before entering the loop.\n"
}